column86: Notes for D-Air loop
Inconsistantly on the % where it spikes
DI in front of Bayonetta for the last hit in order to get the loop going on % where it doesn't spike them up.
Does only work when the D-air hits Bowser's back or if he's already in tumble. Doesn't work with max rage
Sometimes doesn't work and gives a sourhit.
When started at a distance don't DI fully in
DI in front of C. Falcon for the last hit in order to get the loop going on % where it doesn't spike them up
Does only work when the D-air hits Charizard's back or if he's already in tumble.
Gets even more inconsistant with rage. RAR D-air works better with rage
DI in front of D.Pit for the last hit in order to get the loop going on % where it doesn't spike them up.
DI in front of D. Samus for the last hit in order to get the loop going on % where it doesn't spike them up.
Very rarely don't work.
DI in front of DK around the 2nd hit to the loops. Works in the back flawlessly and DK turnsaround. Easier with rage.
Don't DI fully In if it hits in the back. You can fully DI in if you have 100% rage or more.
Rage makes the 2nd loops slightly more inconsistant.
DI in front of Ganondorf for the last hit in order to get the loop going on % where it doesn't spike them up. Doesn't work with max Rage
DI in front of Hero for the last hit in order to get the loop going on % where it doesn't spike them up.
Nana exists
DI in front of Ike for the last hit in order to get the loop going on % where it doesn't spike them up. After 50% rage this doesn't matter
Pretty hard to continue after Joker gets popped up due to hit hitbox shifting.
Sometimes decided to give a sour hit.
First one must be in DeDeDe's back, Second one must hit in front. If you get the loop it's really really easy. Works in the front with Rage
Does only work when the D-air hits K. Rool's back or if he's already in tumble
Extremely inconsistant. DI out between the 3rd and 4th hit. A bit easier with Rage
You can get the sourhit if you land straight untop of Mac, with Rage DI'ing IN can give a sour hit.
You need to wait 2/3 frames before F-smashing, otherwise you'll miss.
You must start the D-air from behind, even in tumble it's pretty hard. Try not DI-in hit 1+2 and DI 3+4 in.
D-air does work in Mewtwo's back, however, it doesn't turnaround so you can't loop unless you get the spike bounce. Numbers are the % when M2 gets spiked up. Max rage doesn't work.
With Rage (150) DI in front works
With Rage (100) DI Behind Mii Gunner works
Must cross-up if you have rage (100%)
Can SDI to avoid the 2nd and 4th hits.
With Rage (100%) You have to DI behind plant.
DI in front of Pit for the last hit in order to get the loop going on % where it doesn't spike them up.
Does only work when the D-air hits R.O.B's back. Turns around if you don't DI in fully. with Max Rage, full DI works fine.
Does only work when the D-air hits Ridley's back or if she's already in tumble, Max rage is extremely inconsistant.
Luma must die first
Sometimes decided to give a sour hit.
DI in front of Samus for the last hit in order to get the loop going on % where it doesn't spike them up.
Does only work when the D-air hits Sheik's back or if she's already in tumble, cannot cross up. Don't turn around so can't combo unless it spikes. The % is the % D-air will pop her up.
Can activate Shield Art Monado and not care.
With Rage (100) You have to DI behind Sonic
Always try to DI on top of squirtle, landing behind him usually gives a sour hit.
Get inconsistant with max Rage (150)
Inconsistant at the front
With rage (150) You have to DI Behind Yoshi
